colonoscopy.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following statements about diarrhoea is incorrect?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Acute diarrhoea is defined as lasting less than 3 weeks","Chronic diarrhoea is defined as lasting more than 4 weeks","Diarrhoea involves passage of loose stools at least three times per day","Secondary lactase deficiency can develop following gastroenteritis","Primary lactase deficiency affects up to 70% of adults worldwide"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis question tests understanding of key definitions and concepts related to diarrhoea. \u003Cstrong\u003EAcute diarrhoea lasting less than 3 weeks\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect - acute diarrhoea is actually defined as lasting less than 14 days, while persistent diarrhoea lasts 14-29 days.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChronic diarrhoea lasting more than 4 weeks\u003C/strong\u003E is correct. This is the widely accepted definition used to guide investigation of underlying causes such as inflammatory bowel disease, coeliac disease, or functional bowel disorders.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDiarrhoea involving at least three loose stools per day\u003C/strong\u003E is correct. This definition from the World Health Organization helps standardise both clinical practice and research.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESecondary lactase deficiency following gastroenteritis\u003C/strong\u003E is correct. The intestinal brush border can be damaged during infection, leading to temporary lactose intolerance that usually resolves in weeks to months.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPrimary lactase deficiency affects up to 70% of adults\u003C/strong\u003E is correct. This condition, also called adult-type hypolactasia, is especially common in Asian, African and South American populations due to genetic factors.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe clinical presentation in the stem illustrates chronic diarrhoea with features suggestive of lactose intolerance - a common condition that should be considered in the differential diagnosis of chronic diarrhoea, particularly when symptoms are worse with dairy products.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Acute diarrhoea lasting less than 2 weeks is most commonly due to infection.","Chronic diarrhoea lasting more than 4 weeks requires systematic investigation of underlying causes.","Lactase deficiency is a common cause of chronic diarrhoea, particularly in certain ethnic groups","Red flags related to chronic diarrhoea should be explored in order to not miss a possible diagnosis of malignancy, especially in the relevant age group"],"references":["Nemeth V, Pfleghaar N. Diarrhea. [Updated 2022 Nov 21]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK448082/","Feleke DG, Chanie ES, Admasu FT, Bahir S, Amare AT, Abate HK. Two-week prevalence of acute diarrhea and associated factors among under five years\u0027 children in Simada Woreda, South Gondar Zone, Northwest Ethiopia, 2021: a multi-central community based cross-sectional study. Pan Afr Med J. 2022 May 7;42:12. doi: 10.11604/pamj.2022.42.12.32599. PMID: 35812258; PMCID: PMC9228916.","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"94065"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15268"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"94065","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/94065"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-08-23T14:40:56+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-08-23T14:41:45+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7959"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"112000"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"